HEADWORD: Equant
<hw>E"quant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aequans</ets>, <ets>-antis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>aequare</ets>: cf.
F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧quant</ets>. See <er>Equate</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Ptolemaic
Astron.)</fld> <def>A circle around whose circumference a planet or the
center of an epicycle was conceived to move uniformly; -- called also
<altname>eccentric equator</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

